# PHASE4-N-M family ‚Äî Ledger seed + live admission ‚Äî invariants sketch

## Framing

PHASE4-N-L-LIVE closed the wire-only half of RO-LIVE-03
(RO-LIVE-04: handshake + tip read + JSONL exit). The remaining
half ‚Äî RO-LIVE-05 (live admission + per-block agreement_verdict
against a real cardano-node peer) ‚Äî is what this cluster family
closes. The wide RO-LIVE-03 flips to enforced when N-M completes.

Per
[[feedback-shell-must-not-overstate-semantic-truth]] the
admission claim is exactly the layer this cluster evidences.
The mechanical work decomposes into two sub-clusters:

- **PHASE4-N-M-UTXO-DECODE** (predecessor) ‚Äî implement the
  cardano-node compact UTxO decoder in the snapshot loader.
  Mechanical-evidence only; no live pass.
- **PHASE4-N-M-LEDGER-SEED** (this cluster) ‚Äî assumes
  UTXO-DECODE is done; ships admission-mode binary wiring +
  snapshot import + per-block agreement_verdict JSONL +
  operator pass.

Both are required to close RO-LIVE-05. The honest sketch below
covers both as one family because they're tightly coupled ‚Äî
splitting the operator into two cluster docs only doubles the
ceremony.

## 0. The prerequisite gap (UTxO decode)

`ade_testkit::harness::snapshot_loader::LoadedSnapshot::to_ledger_state`
currently returns a `LedgerState` with an **empty `UTxOState`**
(see `snapshot_loader.rs:45` ‚Äî *"The UTxO set is empty (compact
format impedance)"*). Reward accounts + delegation + pools +
governance are parsed; UTxO is intentionally skipped because
cardano-node uses a "compact UTxO" CBOR representation that the
loader's CBOR navigator currently `skip`s.

Without the UTxO seed, `admit_via_block_validity` would fail on
the very first incoming live block (every tx input it consumes
would be a UTxO-set miss ‚Üí `Validity(InputNotFound)`). The first
agreement_verdict would be `Diverged` and the binary would halt.

**Therefore PHASE4-N-M-UTXO-DECODE is the hard predecessor.**
There is no clean shortcut:
- Replay-from-genesis is not viable (preprod = ~10M slots; days
  of wall-clock; mainnet = decades).
- Per-block on-demand UTxO via cardano-cli `LocalStateQuery
  --tx-in` is operationally a different system (RPC per input
  instead of local state) and breaks `bootstrap_initial_state`'s
  closed-input contract.
- A hand-crafted toy UTxO would close zero real blocks and
  could give false-divergence signals.

So sub-cluster A ships the compact UTxO codec; sub-cluster B
ships the live-pass binary on top.

## 1. What must always be true

- **I-1 Snapshot import is transactional and authority-fatal.**
  `--ledger-snapshot-import PATH` either imports the snapshot
  successfully into the persistent `SnapshotStore` (and the
  binary proceeds to admission) or fails closed with a
  structured error and exits non-zero. No partial seed; no
  silent fallback to empty UTxO.
- **I-2 Import authority is single-sited.** Exactly one `pub fn`
  in `ade_runtime::snapshot_import` converts a cardano-node
  snapshot tarball/CBOR into an Ade `(LedgerState,
  PraosChainDepState)` pair. Mirrors CN-STORE-07 / CN-NODE-01
  single-authority discipline.
- **I-3 Compact UTxO decode is canonical.** The decoder reads
  every TxIn ‚Üí TxOut entry in the cardano-node compact format,
  builds an Ade `UTxOState`, and re-encoding produces a UTxO map
  with byte-identical `fingerprint` to the source's UTxO
  fingerprint (within the known Rational-precision residual ‚Äî
  see I-7).
- **I-4 Admission mode never bypasses CN-CONS-08.** Every live
  block from the peer's chain-sync / block-fetch goes through
  `admit_via_block_validity`. No "trusted prefix", no
  "header-only fast path", no "skip validation flag".
- **I-5 Per-block agreement_verdict is emitted exactly once per
  admit.** The closed `AgreementVerdict` sum has four variants:
  `Agreed | Lagging | Diverged | InputNotFound`. The verdict is
  derived deterministically from the admit outcome + the peer's
  announced tip in the same chain-sync message.
- **I-6 Diverged is authority-fatal.** A `Diverged` verdict halts
  the binary with the authority-fatal-decode exit code (mirrors
  PHASE4-N-K DC-NODE-04). Diverged means our admit succeeded
  but produced a different `block_hash` than the peer's
  announced block hash at the same slot ‚Äî that's a real chain
  disagreement, not a transient lag.
- **I-7 Known precision residual is recorded, not hidden.** The
  CE-71 reserves residual (949 ADA from `Rational` precision)
  carries into the imported ledger state. The cluster's tier-5
  classification records this explicitly: bit-exact-reserves
  parity with cardano-node is NOT a goal; per-block UTxO admit
  agreement IS the goal. A test asserts the residual stays
  within the documented bound (‚â§ 1 ADA/snapshot).
- **I-8 JSONL admission vocabulary is closed.** Admission mode
  emits a separate closed `AdmissionLogEvent` enum (NOT the
  wire-only `LiveLogEvent`). Admission events include
  `admission_started`, `snapshot_imported`, `bootstrap_complete`,
  `block_received`, `block_admitted`, `agreement_verdict`,
  `admission_halted`, `admission_shutdown`. Wire-only events
  (`handshake_ok`, `peer_tip_read`, ...) are EMITTED TOO in
  admission mode (the wire layer is the same), via a unified
  event-sum trait.

## 2. What must never be possible

- **¬¨P-1** Calling `bootstrap_initial_state` with
  `genesis_initial: None` in admission mode if no snapshot
  exists in the `snapshot_store`. The binary fails closed.
- **¬¨P-2** Producing a non-empty `UTxOState` from a source
  whose UTxO CBOR was not actually decoded (e.g., a stub that
  returns `BTreeMap::new()` on parse error). The decoder fails
  loud or returns the real map; never silently empty.
- **¬¨P-3** Emitting `agreement_verdict { Agreed }` if the
  admitted block's hash differs from the peer's announced hash
  at that slot. Agreement is byte-equality, not "we accepted
  some block".
- **¬¨P-4** Emitting `agreement_verdict` for a block that was
  NOT admitted via `admit_via_block_validity`. The verdict is
  scoped to the admit-authority's actual output.
- **¬¨P-5** Silently retrying a `Diverged` verdict. Diverged is
  authority-fatal.
- **¬¨P-6** Wire-only mode emitting admission events. The
  separation discipline shipped at PHASE4-N-L-LIVE stays
  intact; admission-mode-only events live in a separate enum
  with its own CI grep gate.
- **¬¨P-7** Bypassing the snapshot importer with hand-crafted
  ledger state in production code. Tests may construct minimal
  `LedgerState`s; production code goes through the importer.

## 3. What must remain identical across executions

- Snapshot import determinism: same `(snapshot bytes)` ‚Üí same
  `(LedgerState, PraosChainDepState)` byte-identical across two
  runs.
- UTxO decode determinism: same compact UTxO bytes ‚Üí same
  `BTreeMap<TxIn, TxOut>` (byte-identical via `fingerprint`).
- Agreement verdict determinism: given the same
  `(admit_outcome, peer_announced_tip)` pair, the verdict is
  the same. The verdict reducer is pure.
- Admission JSONL determinism: with a `DeterministicClock` +
  recorded event vector, the JSONL output is byte-identical
  across two replays.

## 4. What must be replay-equivalent

- The admission reducer (admit + verdict derivation) replayed
  against a recorded `(block, peer_tip)` corpus produces the
  same `(LedgerState fingerprint, AgreementVerdict)` sequence.

## 5. State transitions in scope

```text
snapshot_import::import_cardano_node_snapshot(path)
  -> Result<(LedgerState, PraosChainDepState, SlotNo), SnapshotImportError>
  // SOLE pub fn returning a real-cardano-node-derived initial state.
  // Composes compact_utxo_decode + the existing snapshot_loader
  // (DState, PState, VState, EpochState, ProtoParams).

ade_node::admission::run_admission(cli)
  -> ExitCode
  // 1. If --ledger-snapshot-import PATH supplied: import ‚Üí encode
  //    via framing::encode_snapshot ‚Üí write via
  //    PersistentSnapshotCache::capture at snapshot's slot.
  // 2. Call bootstrap_initial_state (warm-start branch).
  // 3. Spawn N2nDialer for each --peer.
  // 4. Run run_node_until_shutdown.
  // 5. Per AdmittedBlock effect: derive AgreementVerdict from
  //    peer's announced tip; emit admission JSONL event.
  // 6. Diverged verdict ‚Üí halt fatal.
  // 7. SIGINT/SIGTERM ‚Üí drain + shutdown.

verdict::derive(admit_outcome, peer_announced_tip)
  -> AgreementVerdict
  // pure; closed sum
```

## 6. TCB color hypothesis

- **BLUE (new in N-M-UTXO-DECODE):**
  - `ade_codec::shelley::compact_utxo` ‚Äî pure compact-UTxO
    CBOR decoder.
- **GREEN (new in N-M-LEDGER-SEED):**
  - `ade_runtime::snapshot_import` ‚Äî single-authority importer
    composing the BLUE compact_utxo decoder + existing
    snapshot_loader sub-parsers.
  - `ade_node::admission::verdict` ‚Äî pure verdict derivation
    over `(admit_outcome, peer_tip)`.
  - `ade_node::admission_log::{event, writer}` ‚Äî closed
    `AdmissionLogEvent` enum + writer.
- **RED (new in N-M-LEDGER-SEED):**
  - `ade_node::admission` ‚Äî tokio-driven admission-mode entry
    point.
  - `ade_node::main` ‚Äî extended with admission routing.

## 7. Decisions on framing questions

| # | Question | Recommendation |
|---|----------|----------------|
| 1 | Where does the compact UTxO decoder live? | `ade_codec::shelley::compact_utxo` (BLUE). Per-era variants under one module. Promoted via single pub fn `decode_compact_utxo_state(bytes, era) -> Result<UTxOState, _>`. |
| 2 | Snapshot source format | Cardano-node 11.0.1 LedgerDB tarball, as the existing testkit `LoadedSnapshot::from_tarball` accepts. The user has these via the `.cardano-node-preprod/db/ledger/` directory. |
| 3 | Snapshot slot ‚Üî peer tip alignment | The imported snapshot's `last_applied_slot` becomes the chain-sync intersection point. The dialer issues `FindIntersect([snapshot_slot])` to anchor. |
| 4 | What about a stale snapshot? | If `peer_tip - snapshot_slot > K_security` (3 * 2160 = 6480 blocks), the peer's chain-sync responds with `IntersectNotFound`. We treat this as authority-fatal `SnapshotTooStale` ‚Üí operator must re-export a fresher snapshot. |
| 5 | Block admission rate | We admit blocks as fast as they arrive on chain-sync + block-fetch. No throttle. The 1-tx-1-thread test-set works; live should saturate at the wire's bandwidth √ó per-block validity cost. |
| 6 | When does the cluster close? | When the operator captures a 30-minute JSONL log against the local docker preprod showing `agreement_verdict { Agreed }` for ‚â• 90% of admitted blocks (the others may be `Lagging` if our admit lags the peer's tip momentarily ‚Äî `Lagging` is OK; `Diverged` is not). |
| 7 | Genesis cold-start path | Out of scope. Cold-start from genesis requires byron‚Üíshelley‚Üí‚Ä¶‚Üíconway era transitions in `bootstrap`, which is a separate clusterhead. Snapshot-import covers every operational use case. |
| 8 | Tier classification | Tier 1 (semantic): admit-correctness against a real peer is the bounty's core claim. The Rational-precision residual (I-7) is Tier 5 ‚Äî operator-evidence-only, recorded but not gating. |
| 9 | TLS / auth | Still out of scope (¬¨P-8 carried from PHASE4-N-L). Local docker doesn't need it. |

## 8. Registry deltas (planned at /cluster-plan)

### New families
- **DC-IMPORT** ‚Äî derived constraints on snapshot import + UTxO decode.
- **CN-IMPORT** ‚Äî single-authority closure on the importer.
- **DC-ADMIT** ‚Äî derived constraints on admission mode.

### New rules (declared at append; flipped per slice)

- `CN-IMPORT-01` ‚Äî Single snapshot-import authority
  (`ade_runtime::snapshot_import::import_cardano_node_snapshot`).
- `DC-IMPORT-01` ‚Äî Compact UTxO decode is canonical:
  re-encode produces byte-identical UTxO fingerprint.
- `DC-IMPORT-02` ‚Äî Snapshot import is transactional + authority-
  fatal on failure.
- `DC-IMPORT-03` ‚Äî Known Rational-precision residual is bounded
  (‚â§ 1 ADA / snapshot); recorded, not hidden.
- `CN-ADMIT-01` ‚Äî Single admission-mode entry
  (`ade_node::admission::run_admission`).
- `DC-ADMIT-01` ‚Äî Closed `AgreementVerdict` sum:
  `Agreed | Lagging | Diverged | InputNotFound`.
- `DC-ADMIT-02` ‚Äî `agreement_verdict` emitted exactly once per
  admit; never without a prior `admit_via_block_validity` call.
- `DC-ADMIT-03` ‚Äî Diverged is authority-fatal; binary halts.
- `DC-ADMIT-04` ‚Äî Closed admission JSONL vocabulary
  (`AdmissionLogEvent` enum + CI grep on disallowed strings
  outside this enum).

### Strengthenings (recorded at cluster close)

- `T-DET-01.strengthened_in += "PHASE4-N-M-LEDGER-SEED"` ‚Äî
  determinism extends to imported initial state + admission
  verdict.
- `CN-CONS-08.strengthened_in += "PHASE4-N-M-LEDGER-SEED"` ‚Äî
  admit path now driven by real-peer chain-sync + block-fetch
  end-to-end.
- `CN-STORE-07.strengthened_in += "PHASE4-N-M-LEDGER-SEED"` ‚Äî
  materialize path now driven by snapshot-import warm-start.
- `CN-STORE-08.strengthened_in += "PHASE4-N-M-LEDGER-SEED"` ‚Äî
  encode/decode driven by snapshot-import write + bootstrap
  warm-start read.
- `RO-LIVE-05` ‚Üí `enforced` (cluster closes the rule).
- `RO-LIVE-03` ‚Üí `enforced` (wide rule flips when both halves
  close).

## 9. Slice shape (proposed; refine at /cluster-plan)

### Sub-cluster A ‚Äî PHASE4-N-M-UTXO-DECODE

| Slice | Scope | TCB | Effort |
|-------|-------|-----|--------|
| A1 | BLUE `ade_codec::shelley::compact_utxo::decode_alonzo_plus` ‚Äî Conway-era TxOut decoder. | BLUE | medium |
| A2 | BLUE per-era compact-UTxO variants (Babbage / Conway differ in TxOut tagging). | BLUE | medium |
| A3 | Promote `snapshot_loader::to_ledger_state` to populate UTxO; round-trip vs source UTxO fingerprint (CI test). | GREEN | small |
| A4 | Performance: 1.5M+ entry UTxO decode in < 10s on commodity hardware. Profiling slice. | GREEN | small |

### Sub-cluster B ‚Äî PHASE4-N-M-LEDGER-SEED

| Slice | Scope | TCB | Effort |
|-------|-------|-----|--------|
| B1 | GREEN `ade_runtime::snapshot_import::import_cardano_node_snapshot` ‚Äî single-authority importer. CN-IMPORT-01 + DC-IMPORT-01/02/03. | GREEN | small |
| B2 | GREEN `ade_node::admission::verdict` ‚Äî closed `AgreementVerdict` sum + pure derivation reducer. DC-ADMIT-01. | GREEN | small |
| B3 | GREEN `ade_node::admission_log::{event, writer}` ‚Äî closed admission JSONL vocabulary (8 variants). DC-ADMIT-04. | GREEN + CI | small |
| B4 | RED `ade_node::admission` ‚Äî admission-mode tokio runner. Snapshot import ‚Üí write to store ‚Üí bootstrap ‚Üí N2nDialer ‚Üí admit loop ‚Üí verdict emit. CN-ADMIT-01, DC-ADMIT-02/03. | RED | medium |
| B5 | RED `ade_node::main` ‚Äî extend `--mode` dispatch with `admission` arm. `--ledger-snapshot-import PATH` flag. CLI parsing. | RED | small |
| B6 | Hermetic loopback admission test ‚Äî in-process responder pumps a corpus block; assert `agreement_verdict { Agreed }`. | RED + test | medium |
| B7 | Operator pass: 30-min run against local docker preprod; capture admission JSONL log under `docs/clusters/completed/PHASE4-N-M-LEDGER-SEED/`. Closes RO-LIVE-05. | operator-action | small |

Total estimate: A is the bulk (compact UTxO decoder for two eras
= multi-week work). B is roughly a copy of PHASE4-N-L-LIVE's
shape (~3-day cluster) but assumes A is done.

## 10. Honest-scope carry-forward

- **Genesis cold-start** ‚Äî still out of scope. Cold-start from
  byron genesis is a separate effort (would need era-transition
  replay through `bootstrap`).
- **Block production** ‚Äî separate cluster (CN-CONS-06 live half;
  requires KES/VRF/opcert wiring + actually broadcasting a
  forged block + the peer accepting it).
- **Mempool integration** ‚Äî separate cluster (PHASE4-N-E live
  half; tx-submission via live peer).
- **Peer-sharing / tx-submission protocols** ‚Äî out of scope.
- **TLS / authenticated transport** ‚Äî still ¬¨P-8.

## 11. Why this is the next cluster (after consideration)

It's the largest remaining bounty-relevance gap. Tip-following
(RO-LIVE-04) is closed ‚Äî the binary can talk to a real peer.
Validation-against-live-blocks (RO-LIVE-05) is what the bounty
actually wants for "validation agreement"; this cluster ships
it.

The cluster's first 50‚Äì70% of cost is the compact UTxO decoder
(PHASE4-N-M-UTXO-DECODE). That work is gated by no other cluster
and pure-BLUE ‚Äî it's the right next mechanical investment.

## 12. Open scoping question for the user

This sketch separates A (UTxO-decode, multi-week) from B (live
admission, ~3 days). Two viable cluster orderings:

- **A then B** ‚Äî sketch both now; ship A first (closes CI-only
  mechanical evidence); ship B once A lands (closes RO-LIVE-05
  live evidence). Honest sequencing.
- **B-first stub-mode** ‚Äî ship B against a hermetic test
  responder + a tiny hand-crafted snapshot (10 UTxO entries
  matching a curated block) to prove the admission machinery
  wires correctly. RO-LIVE-05 stays open until A lands. Adds
  a temporary `--admission-mode-stub-snapshot` flag that we
  later remove. Risk: introduces a fake path that violates
  [[feedback-shell-must-not-overstate-semantic-truth]]
  unless the hermetic test is clearly scoped as "machinery
  test, not live evidence."

Recommendation: **A then B**. Honest sequencing matches the
project's prior cluster discipline. The temporary stub path is
the kind of fake-path that erodes the invariant story.

Decide at `/cluster-plan` time ‚Äî for now this sketch covers
both as one family doc so the full cost is visible.
